						<div class="postbody">Now it's finally possible to do turns on the Mode 7 map. I achieved this by pre-calculating no less than 1024 HDMA tables -- four for each one of the 256 rotation angles. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br /><img src="http://manuloewe.de/snestuff/projects/furryrpg_build_00220.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><strong>Download:</strong><br /><a href="http://manuloewe.de/snestuff/projects/furryrpg_build_00220.7z" class="postlink">http://manuloewe.de/snestuff/projects/furryrpg_build_00220.7z</a><br /><br />Unfortunately, you can't &quot;fly&quot; forward on any rotation angle yet as the BG is apparently scrolled relative to the northern edge of the Mode 7 GFX, not the first scanline or X/Y center coordinates. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" /> But I'll definitely make that possible somehow, too. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /></div>

					
