						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">byuu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It seems so obvious, but I've seen fan translations that prided themselves on packing everything into unexpanded ROMs, like some sort of demoscene challenge.</div><br />In the case of SNES games, banking could have made it painful to expand those ROMs, depending on how the game handled that.<br /><br />Also I seriously can't believe there isn't a feasible way to do this when many other games probably did it without a ton of precalculated tables (possibly precalculated operations, but not the full thing). Heck, how did F-Zero do it? (and F-Zero isn't using any coprocessors). Because I can't imagine the fully precalculated table method scaling well in the long term.</div>

